\cb3 ### Database Relationships & Constraints\cb1 \
\
\cb3 #### Primary Relationships\cb1 \
\cb3 - **Parents \uc0\u8594  Athletes**: One-to-many (parent can have multiple children)\cb1 \
\cb3 - **Parents \uc0\u8594  Bookings**: One-to-many (parent can have multiple bookings)\cb1 \
\cb3 - **Bookings \uc0\u8594  Athletes**: Many-to-many (semi-private lessons)\cb1 \
\cb3 - **Bookings \uc0\u8594  Focus Areas**: Many-to-many (multiple focus areas per booking)\cb1 \
\cb3 - **Bookings \uc0\u8594  Side Quests**: Many-to-many (multiple side quests per booking)\cb1 \
\
\cb3 #### Cascade Rules\cb1 \
\cb3 - **Parent Deletion**: Cascades to athletes and bookings\cb1 \
\cb3 - **Booking Deletion**: Cascades to booking_athletes, booking_focus_areas, booking_side_quests\cb1 \
\cb3 - **Athlete Deletion**: Blocked if active bookings exist\cb1 \
\
\cb3 #### Indexes for Performance\cb1 \
\cb3 ```sql\cb1 \
\cb3 CREATE INDEX idx_bookings_session_date ON bookings(session_date);\cb1 \
\cb3 CREATE INDEX idx_bookings_parent_id ON bookings(parent_id);\cb1 \
\cb3 CREATE INDEX idx_athletes_parent_id ON athletes(parent_id);\cb1 \
\cb3 CREATE INDEX idx_email_logs_recipient ON email_logs(recipient);\cb1 \
\cb3 CREATE INDEX idx_auth_codes_email ON auth_codes(email);\cb1 \
\cb3 ```\cb1 \
